 in place by woodhouse workspace was a demolition and strip out of existing ceilings flooring partitioning etc mechanical and electrical alterations took place to most of the building including the building management system some of the materials used included glass partitioning with walnut doors and frames for many of the areas within the office space meeting rooms had state of the art audio visual equipment installed and linked to the new furniture the third space included a new teapoint with bespoke booths and benches leading onto a newly refurbished terrace throughout the process acoustic treatment was provided for optimal experience within the meeting rooms design woodhouse workspace  images  expand for additional detailruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacecolumnlinear pendantpantry areapeoplestoolruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacebooth seatinglinear pendantpendant lightingpeoplestoolwoodwood floorwork loungeruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacecarpetmediapeoplerecessed lightingsmall meeting roomwallmounted displayruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacebooth seatingcarpethallwaypendant lightingpeopleruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacelarge meeting roommediapeoplerecessed lightingwallmounted displayruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacepeopleterraceruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacedetailssigns  wayfindingruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacecarpetdetailsruffer llp offices – londonview projectwoodhouse workspacedetails the office snapshots weekly newsletter a weekly digest of the latest office designs delivered every monday view sample company about mediapress feedback contact browse tour offices explore photos browse products our firms our brands partner advertise submit office project request brand profile add job  career listing connect instagram twitter facebook pinterest linkedin   offic